---
/**
 * ai-security/0001 · Figure 4 — "Threat-modeling stepper".
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from the source lesson (figure + svg + figcaption incl. the
 * footnote <sup id="r4b">). Lives as an .astro component (kebab-case SVG attrs are
 * unreliable in MDX). The shared arw + arwG arrowhead markers are embedded inline
 * so the figure renders standalone; the ids match the source DOM.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 640 250"
        role="img"
        aria-label="A four-step threat-modeling stepper for an LLM app: list assets, find entry points where untrusted text enters, mark the trust boundaries, then place a control and name the residual risk on each."
    >
        <defs>
            <marker
                id="arw"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#6b675f"></path></marker
            >
            <marker
                id="arwG"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#2f5d3a"></path></marker
            >
        </defs>
        <text x="320" y="18" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
            >Threat-modeling stepper</text
        >

        <rect
            x="24"
            y="40"
            width="142"
            height="76"
            rx="8"
            fill="#eef2f7"
            stroke="#1f3a5a"
            stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
        <text x="95" y="60" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" font-weight="700" fill="#1f3a5a"
            >1 · Assets</text
        >
        <text x="95" y="78" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.8" fill="#6b675f"
            >tenant data, secrets,</text
        >
        <text x="95" y="89" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.8" fill="#6b675f"
            >system prompt, the</text
        >
        <text x="95" y="100" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.8" fill="#6b675f"
            >ability to act</text
        >

        <line x1="166" y1="78" x2="190" y2="78" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
        <rect
            x="192"
            y="40"
            width="142"
            height="76"
            rx="8"
            fill="#fbecec"
            stroke="#9a2417"
            stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
        <text x="263" y="60" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" font-weight="700" fill="#9a2417"
            >2 · Entry points</text
        >
        <text x="263" y="78" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.8" fill="#6b675f"
            >user input, retrieved</text
        >
        <text x="263" y="89" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.8" fill="#6b675f"
            >docs, tool output,</text
        >
        <text x="263" y="100" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.8" fill="#6b675f"
            >MCP tool descriptions</text
        >

        <line x1="334" y1="78" x2="358" y2="78" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
        <rect
            x="360"
            y="40"
            width="142"
            height="76"
            rx="8"
            fill="#f6eef7"
            stroke="#b5179e"
            stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
        <text x="431" y="60" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" font-weight="700" fill="#b5179e"
            >3 · Boundaries</text
        >
        <text x="431" y="78" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.8" fill="#6b675f"
            >where untrusted &rarr;</text
        >
        <text x="431" y="89" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.8" fill="#6b675f"
            >trusted; each one</text
        >
        <text x="431" y="100" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.8" fill="#6b675f"
            >needs a control</text
        >

        <line x1="502" y1="78" x2="526" y2="78" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
        <rect
            x="498"
            y="128"
            width="142"
            height="76"
            rx="8"
            fill="#e9f3ec"
            stroke="#2f5d3a"
            stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
        <text x="569" y="148" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" font-weight="700" fill="#2f5d3a"
            >4 · Control + residual</text
        >
        <text x="569" y="166" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.8" fill="#6b675f"
            >place the control,</text
        >
        <text x="569" y="177" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.8" fill="#6b675f"
            >map to OWASP, and</text
        >
        <text x="569" y="188" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.8" fill="#6b675f"
            >name what's left over</text
        >
        <line
            x1="569"
            y1="116"
            x2="569"
            y2="126"
            stroke="#2f5d3a"
            stroke-dasharray="3 3"
            marker-end="url(#arwG)"></line>

        <rect x="24" y="150" width="450" height="40" rx="8" fill="#ffffff" stroke="#b5179e"></rect>
        <text x="249" y="167" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" font-weight="700" fill="#b5179e"
            >Key insight: the model is NOT a boundary — it's inside the blast radius.</text
        >
        <text x="249" y="181" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >The boundaries are the retrieval query (ACL) and the tool layer (least privilege +
            egress).</text
        >

        <text x="320" y="232" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" font-style="italic" fill="#9a2417"
            >No control is complete. Layer them, assume breach, and bound the blast radius.</text
        >
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        Run it like any design review, with one adjustment: don't put a boundary on the model. The
        model reads whatever it's handed and answers whoever's asking — it has no notion of <em
            >who</em
        > or <em>trusted</em>.<sup><a href="#s3" id="r4b">3</a></sup>
    </figcaption>
</figure>
